value.value: 胸骨の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the sternum, typically resulting in decreased size
前庭有毛細胞の変性
degeneration or loss of the sensory epithelial cells of the maculae and cristae of the membranous labyrinth of the inner ear which are normally in synaptic contact with the vestibular nerve
前庭有毛細胞の欠如
absence of the sensory epithelial cells of the maculae and cristae of the membranous labyrinth of the inner ear which are normally in synaptic contact with the vestibular nerve
前庭有毛細胞数の異常
abnormal number of cells in the sensory epithelium of the maculae and cristae of the membranous labyrinth of the internal ear
前庭有毛細胞数の増加
increased number of cells in the sensory epithelium of the maculae and cristae of the membranous labyrinth of the internal ear which are normally in synaptic contact with the vestibular nerve
前庭有毛細胞数の減少
decreased number of cells in the sensory epithelium of the maculae and cristae of the membranous labyrinth of the internal ear which are normally in synaptic contact with the vestibular nerve
球形嚢の変性
degeneration or loss of the smaller of the two sacs in the vestibule
球形嚢斑の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the oval neuroepithelial sensory receptor in the anterior wall of the saccule; hair cells of the neuroepithelium support the statoconial membrane and have terminal arborizations of vestibular nerve fibers around their bodies
球形嚢斑の縮退
degeneration or loss of the oval neuroepithelial sensory receptor in the anterior wall of the saccule
卵形嚢の縮退
degeneration or loss of the larger of the two sacs in the vestibule
卵形嚢斑の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the neuroepithelial sensory receptor in the inferolateral wall of the utricle; hair cells of the neuroepithelium support the statoconial membrane and have terminal arborizations of vestibular nerve fibers around their bodies; normally sensitive to linear acceleration in the longitudinal axis of the body and to gravitational influences
卵形嚢の黄斑変性症
degeneration or loss of the neuroepithelial sensory receptor in the inferolateral wall of the utricle
卵形嚢の肥大化
increased size of the larger of the two sacs in the vestibule
卵形嚢の矮小化
reduced size of the larger of the two sacs in the vestibule
鎖骨の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the clavicle, typically resulting in decreased size
鎖骨の矮小化
reduced size of one or both of the doubly curved long bone that forms part of the shoulder girdle and articulates with the sternum and the scapula
鎖骨の欠損
missing one or both of the doubly curved long bone that forms part of the shoulder girdle and articulates with the sternum and the scapula
肩甲骨の短縮
reduced length of either or both of the large, flat bones of the back part of the shoulder
肩甲骨の欠如
missing either or both of the large, flat bones of the back part of the shoulder
肩甲骨孔
presence of a hole in either or both of the large, flat bones of the back part of the shoulder
肩甲骨の矮小化
reduced size of either or both of the large, flat bones of the back part of the shoulder
肩甲骨の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the scapular bone, typically resulting in decreased size
肩峰形態異常
any structural anomaly of the lateral end of the spine of the scapula which projects as a broad flattened process and articulates with the clavicle, and forms the point of the shoulder
肩峰の欠損
lack of the lateral end of the spine of the scapula which projects as a broad flattened process and articulates with the clavicle, and forms the point of the shoulder
肩甲棘の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the triangular ridge on the dorsal aspect of the scapula which separates the supra- from the infraspinatous fossa and where the trapezius and deltoid muscles are attached
大腿骨の伸長
increased length of the long bone of the thigh
大腿骨の欠如
missing the long bone of the thigh
上腕骨の伸長
increased length of one or both of the bones of the forelimb that articulates with the scapula above and the radius and ulna below
上腕骨の短縮
reduced length of one or both of the bones of the forelimb that articulates with the scapula above and the radius and ulna below
上腕骨の欠如
missing one or both of the bones of the forelimb that articulates with the scapula above and the radius and ulna below
三角筋粗面の形態異常
any structural anomaly of a rough elevation at the middle of the lateral side of the shaft of the humerus to which the deltoid muscle attaches
三角筋粗面の欠如
missing the rough elevation at the middle of the lateral side of the shaft of the humerus to which the deltoid muscle attaches
橈骨の短縮
reduced length of the short bone of the lateral forearm
橈骨の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the radius, typically resulting in decreased size
頸骨の伸長
increased length of the medial and larger of the two bones of the lower leg
頚骨の湾曲
increased curvature of the medial and larger of the two bones of the lower leg
尺骨の短縮
reduced length of the medial and larger of the two bones of the forearm
尺骨の欠如
missing the medial and larger of the two bones of the forearm
尺骨の湾曲
increased curvature of the medial and larger of the two bones of the forearm
蝸牛有毛細胞の変性
degeneration or loss of the sensory epithelial cells of the cochlea; these cells are in synaptic contact with the auditory nerve
血管条の縮退
degeneration or loss of the stratified, secretory epithelium which lines the upper part of the cochlear spiral ligament and maintains potassium ion homeostasis in the endolymph
血管条の薄化
reduced thickness of the stratified, secretory epithelium which lines the upper part of the cochlear spiral ligament and maintains potassium ion homeostasis in the endolymph
基底線条細胞の異常
any structural anomaly in the polarized cells which are juxtaposed to fibrocytes in the underlying spiral ligament
線条縁細胞の異常

any structural anomaly in the polarized columnar cells of epithelial origin which cover the lateral surface of the cochlear duct, secrete potassium ions and form a continuous sheet in contact with the endolymph; marginal cells form extensive interdigitations with the basal and intermediate cells in the normal adult stria
線条中間細胞の異常

any structural anomaly in the melanocytes known to migrate from the neural crest during ontogeny to become located between the epithelial marginal cell layer and the mesodermal basal cell layer within the intrastrial space; the predominant cellular component of the electrogenic machinery that generates an endocochlear potential (80-100 mV)
血管条の脈管構造異常
any structural anomaly of the blood vessels supplying the stria vascularis in the cochlea of the inner ear
卵形嚢の欠如
absence of the larger of the two sacs in the vestibule
尺骨の伸長
increased length of the medial and larger of the two bones of the forearm
大腿骨の湾曲
increased curvature of the long bone of the thigh
腓骨の湾曲
increased curvature of the lateral and smaller bone of the lower limb
